{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11581472]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 07:29, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11581472]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 04:09, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Unreferenced|date=March 2021}} '''Kenmotsu''' (監物) refers to a {{ill|Hinkan|ja|品官|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinkan|qq=}} (specialist official) within the [[:en:Ritsuryō|Ritsuryō system]], specifically under the jurisdiction of the [[:en:Ministry of the Center|Ministry of the Center]].
== Duties == Kenmotsu officials were directly subordinate to the Ministry of the Center and were responsible for managing the keys and inspecting the inventory-related duties of various government offices' warehouses. They oversaw the actual handling of keys by officials such as the {{ill|Ten'yaku|ja|典鑰|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ten'yaku|qq=|1=Minor Key-Holder|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11393761}} of the Ministry of the Center, as well as the {{ill|Shuyaku|ja|主鑰|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shuyaku|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in the [[:en:Ministry of the Treasury|Ministry of the Treasury]] and the {{ill|Naizōryō|ja|内蔵寮|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Naizōryō|qq=|1=kuraryou|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11394423}}. Originally, Kenmotsu may have been directly under the emperor as part of the "Shimotsumono-shoku" (下物職). This title was later incorporated into the Ministry of the Center under the Ritsuryō system. The term "Shimotsumono-shoku" persisted as an alternative name for Kenmotsu.
There were initially three grades of Kenmotsu: Dai Kenmotsu (大監物), Chū Kenmotsu (中監物), and Shō Kenmotsu (少監物). However, the Chū Kenmotsu position was later abolished and replaced by the newly established '''Kenmotsu Sakan''' (監物主典), who assisted with administrative duties.
== Ranks and Personnel == * '''Dai Kenmotsu''' (従五位下, Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade): 1 position * '''Chū Kenmotsu''' (従六位上, Junior Sixth Rank, U11er Grade): 4 positions (abolished) * '''Shō Kenmotsu''' (正七位下, Senior Seventh Rank, Lower Grade): 4 positions * '''Kenmotsu Sakan''' (従七位上, Junior Seventh Rank, U11er Grade): Newly established * '''Shisei''' (史生, Clerical officers)
== Related Articles == * {{ill|Government of Japan under the Ritsuryō system|ja|日本の官制|1=structure of the ritsuryō government|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Government of Japan under the Ritsuryō system|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese administrative system|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q8193883}}
